0Musk%20and%20China%20in%20an%20ever-growing%20queue%20of%20buyers.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22jwilkins%40insider.com%20(Joseph%20Wilkins)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fstocks%2Fnvidia-chips-saudi-uae-demand-artificial-intelligence-tech-musk-china-2023-8%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22The%20Fed%20may%20not%20begin%20cutting%20interest%20rates%20until%20mid-2024%2C%20Goldman%20Sachs%20economists%20say%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224456%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20silhouette%20of%20a%20man%20walking%20in%20Goldman%20Sachs%20headquarters%20towards%20a%20screen%20that%20shows%20the%20bank's%20logo.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64b5923fdb902600193553a3%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223342%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EGoldman%20Sachs%20laid%20off%20some%203%2C000%20people%20this%20week.%3Cp%3EREUTERS%2FAndrew%20Kelly%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThe%20Fed's%20most%20aggressive%20policy-tightening%20cycle%20since%20the%201980s%20has%20seen%20interest%20rates%20rise%20from%20near-zero%20to%20over%205%25.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EGoldman%20Sachs%20sees%20the%20central%20bank%20holding%20interest%20rates%20high%20until%20at%20least%20mid-2024.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EEconomists%20at%20the%20Wall%20Street%20bank%20believe%20the%20Fed%20may%20not%20rush%20to%20stimulate%20an%20already-strong%20economy.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EGoldman%20Sachs%20economists%20don't%20expect%20the%20Federal%20Reserve%20to%20start%20cutting%20interest%20rates%20until%20at%20least%20mid-2024%2C%20and%20predict%20the%20central%20bank%20will%20introduce%20steady%20quarter-point%20reductions%20from%20that%20point%20onward.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Fed's%20most%20aggressive%20monetary-tightening%20campaign%20since%20the%201980s%20saw%20interest%20rates%20rise%20from%20near%20zero%20to%20over%205%25%20since%20last%20spring%2C%20in%20efforts%20to%20combat%20rampant%20inflation%20in%20the%20economy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20though%20Goldman%20sees%20rate%20cuts%20as%20the%20natural%20next%20step%20in%20the%20Fed's%20policymaking%2C%20its%20economists%20don't%20see%20this%20happening%20before%20at%20least%20the%20end%20of%20the%20second-quarter%20of%202024%20%E2%80%93%20later%20than%20the%20market%20consensus.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20note%20published%20at%20the%20weekend%2C%20Goldman%20economists%20Jan%20Hatzius%20and%20David%20Mericle%20explained%20the%20reasoning%20behind%20their%20predictions.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNormalization%20is%20not%20a%20particularly%20urgent%20motivation%20for%20cutting%2C%20and%20for%20that%20reason%20we%20also%20see%20a%20significant%20risk%20that%20the%20FOMC%20will%20instead%20hold%20steady%2C%26quot%3B%20they%20wrote.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20FOMC%20might%20not%20cut%20because%20inflation%20might%20not%20fall%20enough%20or%2C%20even%20if%20it%20does%2C%20because%20solid%20growth%2C%20a%20tight%20labor%20market%2C%20and%20a%20further%20easing%20of%20financial%20conditions%20might%20make%20cutting%20seem%20like%20an%20unnecessary%20risk.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETheir%20view%20is%20more%20cautious%20compared%20with%20the%20market%20consensus.%20The%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cmegroup.com%2Fmarkets%2Finterest-rates%2Fcme-fedwatch-tool.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECME%20FedWatch%20Tool%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20captures%20interest-rate%20expectations%20implied%20by%20money-market%20prices%2C%20projects%20the%20Fed%20Funds%20Rate%20to%20maintain%20its%20current%20range%20of%205.25%25%20to%205.50%25%20until%20March%202024%2C%20when%20it%20may%20be%20lowered%20by%2025%20basis%20points.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20Goldman%20economists%20believe%20the%20rate%20cut%20will%20come%20later%20than%20this%2C%20as%20the%20Fed%20may%20not%20