22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22%E2%80%98Umpire%20Cannot%20be%20Subordinate%20to%20Team%20Captain%E2%80%99%3A%20Election%20Commissioners%20Bill%20Raises%20Questions%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F15125309%2FNirvachan-Sadan-TW.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20Union%20government%E2%80%99s%20move%20to%20introduce%20a%20legislation%20proposing%20that%20election%20commissioners%20will%20be%20selected%20by%20a%20panel%20led%20by%20the%20prime%20minister%2C%20with%20the%20leader%20of%20the%20opposition%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20and%20a%20Union%20cabinet%20minister%20as%20members%2C%20has%20raised%20concerns%20about%20the%20overriding%20executive%20control%20over%20the%20poll%20body.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20legislation%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fprsindia.org%2Ffiles%2Fbills_acts%2Fbills_parliament%2F2023%2FBill_Text_Chief_Election_Commissioner_and_other_Election_Commissioners_Bill_2023.pdf%5C%22%3EThe%20Chief%20Election%20Commissioner%20and%20Other%20Election%20Commissioners%20(Appointment%2C%20Conditions%20of%20Service%20and%20Term%20of%20Office)%20Bill%2C%202023%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20was%20introduced%20on%20Thursday%20(August%2010)%20by%20the%20Union%20Ministry%20for%20Law%20and%20Justice%20in%20the%20Rajya%20Sabha%2C%20just%20a%20day%20before%20the%20parliament%E2%80%99s%20monsoon%20session%20was%20to%20draw%20to%20a%20close.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Bill%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fnew-bill-selection-of-election-commissioners%5C%22%3Eintroduced%20as%20opposition%20members%20protested%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20calling%20the%20legislation%20an%20attempt%20by%20the%20ruling%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20(BJP)%20to%20control%20the%20election%20body.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20comes%20months%20after%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fsupreme-court-says-committee-of-pm-leader-of-opposition-cji-should-appoint-election-commissioners%5C%22%3Econstitution%20bench%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20ruled%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20March%20that%20election%20commissioners%20should%20be%20appointed%20by%20the%20president%20based%20on%20advice%20from%20a%20committee%20comprising%20the%20prime%20minister%2C%20the%20leader%20of%20opposition%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20and%20the%20chief%20justice%20of%20India%20(CJI).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20bench%20noted%20that%20its%20order%20was%20meant%20to%20fill%20a%20constitutional%20vacuum%20in%20the%20absence%20of%20a%20parliamentary%20law%20to%20lay%20down%20the%20selection%20procedure%20for%20election%20commissioners.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20the%20Bill%20states%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Bill%20repeals%20the%20Election%20Commission%20(Conditions%20of%20Service%20of%20Election%20Commissioners%20and%20Transaction%20of%20Business)%20Act%2C%201991.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Article%20324%20of%20the%20constitution%2C%20the%20election%20commission%20will%20consist%20of%20the%20chief%20election%20commissioner%20(CEC)%20and%20such%20number%20of%20other%20election%20commissioners%20(ECs)%20as%20the%20president%20may%20decide.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20CEC%20and%20other%20ECs%20are%20appointed%20by%20the%20president.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20new%20Bill%2C%20while%20keeping%20the%20same%20composition%20of%20the%20election%20commission%2C%20adds%20that%20the%20CEC%20and%20other%20ECs%20will%20be%20appointed%20by%20the%20president%20on%20the%20recommendation%20of%20a%20selection%20committee.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Bill%20states%20the%20selection%20committee%20will%20consist%20of%20the%20prime%20minister%20as%20the%20chairperson%3B%20the%20leader%20of%20opposition%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%2C%20as%20member%3B%20and%20a%20Union%20cabinet%20minister%20to%20be%20nominated%20by%20the%20prime%20minister%2C%20also%20as%20a%20member.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20Read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fall-the-vital-stats-about-parliaments-monsoon-session%5C%22%3EAll%20the%20Vital%20Stats%20About%20Parliament%E2%80%99s%20Monsoon%20Session%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20adds%20that%20a%20search%20committee%20for%20election%20commissioners%20will%20be%20headed%20by%20the%20cabinet%20secretary%2C%20with%20two%20members%20who%20are%20not%20below%20the%20rank%20of%20secretary%20to%20the%20Government%20of%20India.%20They%20will%20prepare%20a%20panel%20of%20five%20persons%20for%20consideration%20by%20the%20selection%20committee.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%201991%20Act%20stated%20that%20the%20salary%20of%20the%20ECs%20will%20be%20equal%20to%20that%20of%20a%20Supreme%20Court%20judge%2C%20the%20new%20Bill%20states%20that%20salary%2C%20allowance%2C%20and%20service%20conditions%20of%20the%20CEC%20and%20other%20ECs%20will%20be%20the%20same%20as%20that%20of%20the%20cabinet%20secretary.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20bill%20also%20provides%20that%20the%20CEC%20and%20other%20ECs%20will%20not%20be%20eligible%20for%20re-appointment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20business%20of%20the%20election%20commission%20will%20be%20conducted%20unanimously%20and%20if%20a%20difference%20of%20opinion%20arises%2C%20it%20will%20be%20decided%20through%20a%20majority.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESupreme%20Court%20judgement%20%E2%80%98interim%E2%80%99%20was%20in%20%E2%80%98spirit%20of%20Constituent%20Assembly%E2%80%99%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20opposition%20members%20have%20raised%20concerns%20that%20the%20new%20legislation%20will%20allow%20the%20BJP%20government%20to%20rule%20the%20poll%20body%20by%20removing%20the%20CJI%20as%20suggested%20in%20the%20SC-appointed%20panel%2C%20former%20election%20commission%20officials%20and%20judges%20said%20that%20the%20apex%20court%20order%20was%20always%20meant%20to%20be%20replaced%20by%20a%20parliamentary%20law.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFormer%20Supreme%20Court%20judge%20Madan%20B.%20Lokur%20said%20to%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%20%3C%2Fem%3Ethat%20the%20%E2%80%9Cspirit%20of%20the%20judgement%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20was%20an%20expression%20of%20the%20views%20of%20the%20Constituent%20Assembly.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20spirit%20of%20the%20judgement%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20was%20an%20expression%20of%20the%20views%20of%20the%20Constituent%20Assembly.%20The%20Constituent%20Assembly%20was%20quite%20clear%20that%20the%20election%20machinery%20should%20be%20outside%20the%20control%20of%20the%20executive%20government.%20The%20Supreme%20Court%20attempted%20this%20in%20its%20judgement%20but%20while%20enacting%20a%20law%2C%20the%20wisdom%20of%20parliament%20was%20otherwise%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20added%20that%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20order%20had%20also%20stated%20that%20that%20the%20norm%20by%20which%20the%20CJI%20is%20a%20member%20of%20the%20selection%20committee%20%E2%80%9Cwill%20continue%20to%20hold%20good%20till%20a%20law%20is%20made%20by%20the%20parliament.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20one%20sense%2C%20therefore%2C%20it%20would%20not%20be%20correct%20to%20say%20that%20the%20chief%20justice%20of%20India%20has%20been%20replaced%20by%20a%20cabinet%20minister%2C%20since%20the%20arrangement%20made%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20was%20only%20interim%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20Read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fdecoding-the-supreme-courts-election-commission-judgment%5C%22%3EDecoding%20the%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20Election%20Commission%20Judgment%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%E2%80%98Cannot%20have%20umpire%20subordinate%20to%20the%20team%20captain%E2%80%99%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20former%20chief%20election%20commissioner%20who%20did%20not%20wish%20to%20be%20named%20said%20that%20the%20most%20concerning%20aspect%20of%20the%20new%20legislation%20is%20the%20downgrading%20of%20the%20status%20of%20election%20commissioners%20as%20well%20as%20the%20CEC%20from%20being%20at%20par%20with%20Supreme%20Court%20judges%20to%20that%20of%20cabinet%20secretary.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20fact%20is%20that%20the%20cabinet%20secretary%20is%20directly%20under%20the%20government.%20So%20a%20constitutional%20body%20like%20the%20election%20commission%2C%20that%20is%20supposed%20to%20call%20even%20the%20ministers%20and%20prime%20minister%20to%20discipline%20if%20it%20comes%20to%20it%2C%20how%20can%20you%20equate%20that%20office%20with%20the%20cabinet%20secretary%20who%20is%20clearly%20subordinate%20to%20the%20government%3F%E2%80%9D%20he%20asked.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9C%5BThe%5D%20cabinet%20secretary%20may%20be%20the%20highest%20civil%20servant%20in%20the%20country%2C%20but%20is%20directly%20under%20the%20government.%20Giving%20election%20commissioners%20the%20status%20of%20judges%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20gives%20them%20a%20lot%20more%20leverage%20vis-a-vis%20the%20political%20class%20with%20which%20they%20are%20to%20deal%2C%20which%20is%20not%20so%20when%20they%20are%20equated%20as%20cabinet%20secretary.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CYou%20cannot%20have%20an%20umpire%20who%20is%20subordinate%20to%20the%20team%20captain%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFormer%20chief%20election%20commissioner%20T.S.%20Krishna%20Murthy%20further%20said%20that%20this%20reduction%20in%20status%20for%20election%20commissioners%20has%20not%20been%20explained%20in%20the%20Bill.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CReduction%20of%20the%20status%20of%20election%20commissioners%20from%20that%20of%20Supreme%20Court%20judge%20to%20cabinet%20secretary%20has%20not%20been%20explained.%20This%20is%20a%20small%20matter%20financially%2C%20but%20it%20is%20likely%20to%20generate%20controversy%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said%20to%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EChecking%20executive%20control%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKrishna%20Murthy%20added%20that%20while%20the%20Bill%20%E2%80%9Cseems%20to%20comply%20with%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20directions%E2%80%9D%2C%20some%20changes%20could%20have%20been%20made%20to%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20collegium%20is%20an%20improvement%2C%20but%20instead%20of%20having%20a%20cabinet%20minister%2C%20they%20could%20consider%20having%20the%20speaker%20%5Bof%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%5D%2C%20a%20retired%20CJI%20or%20an%20eminent%20jurist%20if%20there%20is%20any%20objection%20to%20having%20the%20CJI%20or%20his%20nominee%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20Read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fjustice-a-p-shah-powerful-executive-has-sidelined-all-institutions-this-is-how-democracy-dies%5C%22%3EJustice%20A.P.%20Shah%3A%20Powerful%20Executive%20Has%20Sidelined%20All%20Institutions%2C%20This%20is%20How%20Democracy%20Dies%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFormer%20chief%20election%20commissioner%20N.%20Gopalaswami%20said%20that%20the%20inclusion%20of%20the%20leader%20of%20opposition%20in%20the%20selection%20committee%20is%20an%20%E2%80%9Cimprovement%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CEarlier%2C%20only%20the%20government%20used%20to%20decide%2C%20now%20there%20is%20the%20leader%20of%20the%20opposition%20being%20brought%20in.%20This%20is%20an%20improvement%20over%20the%20earlier%20arrangement%2C%20as%20there%20is%20a%20chance%20for%20someone%20to%20agree%20or%20disagree%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKrishna%20Murthy%20added%2C%20however%2C%20that%20as%20the%20Bill%20provides%20for%20selection%20from%20%E2%80%98secretaries%20with%20election%20experience%E2%80%99%2C%20it%20will%20give%20an%20impression%20that%20it%20is%20open%20to%20only%20a%20certain%20section%20of%20bureaucracy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIndependence%20dependent%20on%20political%20climate%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20a%20former%20election%20commissioner%2C%20the%20presence%20of%20the%20CJI%20on%20the%20selection%20panel%20does%20not%20assure%20independe