20don't%20mean%20the%20blood-sucking%20immortal%20beings%20seen%20in%20movies%20and%20shows%20like%20Twilight%20or%20True%20Blood%2C%20who%20roam%20around%20in%20full%20flesh%20looking%20for%20their%20next%20victims.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFindings%20do%20suggest%2C%20however%2C%20that%20many%20cultures%20have%20shared%20a%20belief%20that%20the%20dead%20could%20come%20back%20to%20haunt%20the%20living.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERemains%20throughout%20human%20history%20have%20been%20buried%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fvampire-burial-rock-mouth-meant-prevent-rising-dead-2022-9%5C%22%3Estones%20in%20their%20mouths%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20sickles%20across%20their%20throats%2C%20or%20nailed%20to%20the%20ground.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20skeleton%20is%20seen%20with%20a%20sickle%20around%20its%20neck%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F63205c88e8b500001850f6b0%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EIndividual%2049%2F2012%20(30-39%20year%20old%20female)%20is%20shown%20with%20a%20sickle%20placed%20across%20her%20neck.%3Cp%3EAny%20Scott%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EArchaeologists%20often%20assign%20these%20unusual%20burial%20practices%20to%20some%20sort%20of%20%26quot%3Brevenant%26quot%3B%20or%20%26quot%3Bvampire%26quot%3B%20local%20lore.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20is%20probably%20what%20happened%20in%20New%20England%20around%20the%20early%201800s%20when%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.smithsonianmag.com%2Fhistory%2Fthe-great-new-england-vampire-panic-36482878%2F%5C%22%3E%26quot%3Bvampire%20panic%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%20seems%20to%20have%20swept%20the%20area%2C%20200%20years%20after%20the%20Witch%20Panic%2C%20the%20Smithsonian%20magazine%20reported%20in%202012.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBaker's%20skeleton%20isn't%20the%20only%20%26quot%3Bvampire%26quot%3B%20remains%20found%20in%20the%20area.%20Archaeologists%20point%20to%20the%