nt%20released%20Monday%20surveyed%202%2C003%20HR%20professionals%20and%20decision-makers%20in%20the%20UK%20from%20June%20to%20July%202023%2C%20and%20found%20that%20employers%20are%20giving%20counteroffers%20at%20a%20higher%20rate%20than%20in%C2%A0%20previous%20years.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAround%2040%25%20of%20employers%20have%20given%20a%20counteroffer%20in%20the%20past%2012%20months%20and%20just%20over%20half%20said%20they've%20offered%20a%20higher%20number%20of%20counteroffers%20than%20in%20previous%20years.%20A%20quarter%20of%20employers%20expect%20to%20give%20even%20more%20counteroffers%20in%20the%20next%20year.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlmost%20half%20of%20employers%20say%20counteroffers%20are%20effective%20in%20retaining%20employees%20for%20at%20least%2012%20months.%20Some%2040%25%20say%20they%20do%20this%20by%20exceeding%20pay%20offers%20given%20by%20other%20employers%2C%20while%2038%25%20said%20they%20match%20the%20offers%20of%20other%20employers.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHalf%20of%20employers%20are%20planning%20to%20use%20counteroffers%20in%20the%20next%20year%20to%20retain%20staff%20for%20their%20company%20knowledge%20and%20technical%20skills%2C%20the%20CIPD's%20survey%20found.%2038%25%20say%20they%20do%20it%20to%20avoid%20the%20hassle%20of%20finding%20a%20replacement.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Finvestor.ajg.com%2Fnews%2Fnews-details%2F2023%2FEmployee-Retention-Outranks-Revenue-and-Sales-Growth-as-Employers-Top-Operational-Priority-New-Gallagher-Study-Finds%2Fdefault.aspx%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esimilar%20report%20from%20Gallagher%20in%20the%20US%3C%2Fa%3E%20found%20that%20employers%20currently%20see%20retaining%20employees%20as%20their%20number%20one%20priority%20right%20now%2C%20and%20said%20that%20%26quot%3Bemployers%20are%20adjusting%20compensation%20and%20benefits%20to%20improve%20retention%20rates.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20employees%20leave%20a%20business%2C%20th