5C%22%3ESwedish%20bearings%20maker%20SKF%20said%20on%20Tuesday%20its%20factory%20in%20Lutsk%2C%20Ukraine%20was%20hit%20by%20a%20missile%20overnight%2C%20killing%20three%20employees.Ukrainian%20officials%20said%20Russian%20air%20strikes%20had%20hit%20two%20western%20regions%20of%20Ukraine%20and%20other%20areas%20on%20Tuesday%2C%20killing%20three%20people%20and%20wounding%20more%20than%20a%20dozen.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Feurope%2Fmissile-hits-swedish-skf-factory-in-ukraine-killing-three%2Farticleshow%2F102747532.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fm-timesofindia-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fm.timesofindia.com%2Fworld%2Feurope%2Fmissile-hits-swedish-skf-factory-in-ukraine-killing-three%2Famp_articleshow%2F102747532.cms%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fm.timesofindia.com%2Fworld%2Feurope%2Fmissile-hits-swedish-skf-factory-in-ukraine-killing-three%2Famp_articleshow%2F102747532.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Review%3A%20Irfan%20Habib%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%98Maulana%20Azad%3A%20A%20Life%E2%80%99%20Is%20a%20Voice%20of%20Reason%20and%20Unity%20in%20Times%20of%20Hate%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F07%2F28185829%2Fcollage-13.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20these%20times%20of%20spreading%20hate%2C%20it%20is%20balm%20for%20the%20soul%20to%20hear%20the%20voice%20of%20reason%2C%20for%20Maulana%20Abul%20Kalam%20Azad%E2%80%99s%20voice%20was%20the%20voice%20of%20reason%20infused%20with%20compassion.%20Moreover%2C%20as%20it%20was%20a%20voice%20that%20spoke%20only%20in%20Urdu%2C%20Arabic%20and%20Persian%2C%20S.%20Irfan%20Habib%E2%80%99s%20work%20in%20translating%20the%20evolution%20of%20thoughts%20in%20English%20to%20the%20lay%20reader%20(as%20against%20academics)%20stands%20as%20an%20outstanding%20contribution%20to%20national%20integration.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20voice%20had%20a%20most%20unlikely%20origin.%20Azad%E2%80%99s%20family%20had%20migrated%20from%20India%20to%20the%20Hejaz%20in%20the%20mid-1800s%20as%20they%20foresaw%20that%20the%20India%20of%20the%20Mughals%2C%20where%20they%20had%20flourished%2C%20had%20run%20out%20of%20its%20time.%20Theocratic%20and%20conservative%2C%20the%20family%20moved%20to%20Makkah%20(Mecca).%20Moinuddin%20Ahmed%2C%20the%20future%20Maulana%20Azad%2C%20was%20born%20there%20in%201888%20and%20grew%20up%20there%20till%20the%20age%20of%2017%20when%20the%20family%20moved%20again%20to%20Calcutta%20(Kolkata).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20206px)%2085vw%2C%20206px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F15153015%2Fimage-1223-206x300.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22206%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F15153015%2Fimage-1223-206x300.png%20206w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F15153015%2Fimage-1223.png%20373w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-668222%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22300%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98Maulana%20Azad%3A%20A%20Life%E2%80%99%20by%20S.%20Irfan%20Habib%20(Aleph%2C%20February%202023)%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHis%20education%20was%20traditional%20and%20imbued%20with%20religious%20dogma%2C%20initially%20under%20his%20father%2C%20a%20renowned%20scholar%20of%20divinity%2C%20and%20then%20at%20the%20hands%20of%20maulanas%20and%20maulvis%20after%20the%20family%20returned%20to%20India.%20He%20was%20to%20write%20later%20in%20%3Cem%3EGhubar-i-khatir%20(The%20Dust%20of%20Memories)%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20a%20collection%20of%20letters%20and%20essays%2C%20%E2%80%9CAll%20my%20childhood%20was%20spent%20in%20the%20midst%20of%20people%20who%20were%20tradition-bound%20(%3Cem%3Eqadamatparast%3C%2Fem%3E)%2C%20where%20there%20was%20not%20even%20the%20slightest%20opening%20for%20any%20outside%20influence%E2%80%9D%20(pp.185-186).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CDisgusted%E2%80%9D%2C%20says%20the%20author%2C%20by%20the%20blind%20adoration%20given%20to%20his%20father%20by%20his%20Sufi%20%3Cem%3Emurid%3C%2Fem%3Es%20(followers)%2C%20the%20young%20Mohiuddin%20turned%20to%20the%20more%20progressive%2C%20scientific%20rationalism%20of%20Sir%20Syed%20Ahmed%20Khan%2C%20which%2C%20however%2C%20remained%20Islam-oriented%20and%20Muslim-centric%20and%20led%20to%20his%20drifting%20away%20from%20the%20Aligarh%20path%20which%20he%20later%20excoriated.%20To%20this%20was%20added%20a%20fervent%20anti-colonial%20passion%20engendered%20by%20Azad%E2%80%99s%20wide%20travels%20as%20a%20young%20man%20in%20West%20Asia%2C%20then%20steeped%20in%20Wahhabism%20but%20shaken%20by%20the%20radical%20thinking%20of%20Jamaluddin%20Afghani%2C%20Rashid%20Rida%2C%20Mohammad%20Abduh%20and%20other%20reformers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHis%20instinctive%20reaction%20was%20to%20explore%20the%20path%20to%20%E2%80%9Cunbelief%E2%80%9D.%20He%20then%20thought%20%E2%80%9Cthat%20what%20was%20always%20believed%20to%20be%20religion%20was%20merely%20a%20picture%20of%20our%20superstitions%20and%20misapprehensions%2C%20not%20religion%E2%80%9D%20(p.77).%20When%2C%20after%20much%20cogitation%2C%20he%20returned%20to%20Islam%20he%20concluded%20that%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20practice%20of%20love%2C%20regardless%20of%20the%20distinction%20of%20caste%2C%20creed%20or%20nationality%E2%80%9D%20constitute%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20basic%20teachings%20of%20the%20Quran%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E(%3Cem%3ETarjuman%20al-Quran%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20the%20first%20volume%20of%20a%20trilogy%20of%20religious%20commentary%2C%20initially%20written%20in%201915%2C%20destroyed%20by%20the%20colonial%20authority%2C%20rewritten%20several%20times%20over%2C%20polished%20and%20revised%2C%20and%20eventually%20published%20only%20some%2015%20years%20later.%20An%20updated%20version%20came%20after%20his%20release%20from%20Ahmednagar%20Fort%20in%201945).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20exploration%20of%20different%20interpretations%20of%20basic%20Islamic%20texts%20in%20the%20light%20of%20rationalism%20(%3Cem%3Eijtihad%3C%2Fem%3E)%20became%20gradually%20but%20definitively%20the%20drumbeat%20of%20Azad%E2%80%99s%20thinking.%20His%20impassioned%20anti-colonialism%20led%20to%20his%20starting%20and%20editing%20two%20periodic%20journals%2C%20%3Cem%3EAl-Hilal%3C%2Fem%3E%20and%20%3Cem%3EAl-Balagh%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%20that%20sounded%20the%20call%20to%20break%20the%20fetters%20of%20British%20colonialism%20and%2C%20because%20of%20their%20widespread%20resonance%2C%20particularly%20in%20the%20Muslim%20community%2C%20led%20to%20their%20being%20forcibly%20closed%20and%20the%20editor%20being%20sent%20into%20exile%20to%20a%20small%20tribal%20village%20near%20Ranchi.%20It%20was%20the%20first%20of%20a%20series%20of%20imprisonments%20that%20totalled%20nearly%20eight%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHis%20earliest%20works%2C%20%3Cem%3ETazkirah%3C%2Fem%3E%20(Reminiscences)%20and%20%3Cem%3EKahani%3C%2Fem%3E%20(Story)%2C%20contained%20reflections%20on%20his%20family%20and%20his%20upbringing%20and%20were%20complemented%20by%20stray%20epistolatory%20references%20in%20his%20%3Cem%3EGhubar-i-Khatir%3C%2Fem%3E.%20Referring%20to%20these%20and%20others%E2%80%99%20memoirs%2C%20Azad%20remarks%20that%20much%20autobiographical%20writing%20is%20%E2%80%9Cegotistical%E2%80%9D.%20He%20appears%20to%20think%2C%20according%20to%20the%20author%20%2C%20that%20%E2%80%9Cmost%20of%20our%20self-effacing%20behaviour%20is%20actually%20a%20manifestation%20of%20our%20egoism.%E2%80%9D%20The%20world%2C%20writes%20Azad%2C%20%E2%80%9Cdoes%20not%20get%20time%20to%20measure%20their%20ego%20and%20is%20overwhelmed%20by%20its%20frank%20and%20informal%20appearance.%E2%80%9D%20(p.187)%20As%20the%20writer%20of%20my%20recent%20memoirs%20that%20have%20been%20described%20as%20unusually%20%E2%80%9Cfrank%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9Chonest%E2%80%9D%2C%20I%20stand%20humbled!%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhistory%2Fmaulana-azad-always-stressed-on-humanity-its-a-lesson-we-need-now-more-than-ever%5C%22%3EMaulana%20Azad%20Always%20Stressed%20on%20Humanity.%20It%E2%80%99s%20a%20Lesson%20We%20Need%20Now%20More%20Than%20Ever.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHabib%2C%20therefore%2C%20focusses%20on%20Azad%E2%80%99s%20intellectual%20evolution%2C%20ranging%20from%20Islamic%20civilisation%20to%20Islamic%20learning%2C%20and%20covering%20different%20schools%20of%20Islamic%20thought%2C%20Islamic%20mysticism%20and%20Islamic%20science%2C%20climaxing%20in%20Islamic%20nationalism.%20He%20was%20bewitched%20by%20the%20Mu%E2%80%99tazila%20school%20of%20philosophy%20that%20%E2%80%9Csought%20a%20reconciliation%20of%20faith%20with%20reason.%20This%20synthesis%20of%C2%A0%20Muslim%20theology%20with%20Greek%20logic%20gave%20birth%20to%20a%20theological%20science%20called%20ilm-i-Kalam%E2%80%9D.(p.74)%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAzad%20also%20echoed%20the%20radical%20Jamaluddin%20Afghani%2C%20who%2C%20on%20a%20visit%20to%20India%2C%20declared%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20Muslims%20in%20India%20have%20applied%20the%20desire%20to%20defend%20religion%2C%20or%20religious%20zeal%2C%20in%20a%20very%20bad%20way%E2%80%A6They%20believe%20they%20must%2C%20out%20of%20religious%20zeal%2C%20hate%20and%20abominate%20what%20was%20connected%20with%20opponent%E2%80%99s%20faith%2C%20even%20though%20these%20things%20were%20sciences%20and%20arts%E2%80%9D.%20(pp.%2084-85).%20Afghani%20further%20argued%20that%20there%20was%20no%20need%20to%20reinterpret%20Islam%2C%20as%20Sir%20Syed%20had%20done%2C%20%E2%80%9Cto%20make%20it%20(Islam)%20compatible%20with%20the%20requirements%20of%20modern%20science%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfghani%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%9Cmission%20was%20to%20awaken%20Muslims%20from%20obscurantism%20and%20encourage%20them%20to%20embrace%20Western%20science%20and%20rationalism%2C%20%3Cem%3Ewhich%20he%20considered%20inherent%20in%20the%20Quran%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%9D%20(p.80%2C%20italics%20added).%20So%20too%2C%20Azad%20%E2%80%9Cfound%20it%20fallacious%20to%20say%20that%20Islam%20and%20modern%20science%20are%20contradictory%E2%80%9D%20and%20blamed%20the%20ulema%2C%20declaring%20them%20%E2%80%9Ca%20hopeless%20lot%E2%80%A6We%20have%20no%20alternative%20but%20to%20ignore%20rigid%20thinking%20altogether%2C%20focusing%20on%20the%20creation%20of%20a%20new%20mind%E2%80%9D%20(p.%2081)%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20contradistinction%20to%20those%20of%20his%20fellow%20Indian%20Muslims%20who%20were%20concerned%20over%20the%20prospect%20of%20the%20Muslims%20becoming%C2%A0%20an%20oppressed%20minority%20in%20the%20very%20land%20they%20had%20once%20ruled%2C%20Azad%20held%2C%20%E2%80%9CHindus%20and%20Muslims%20must%20unite%20in%20a%20manner%20that%20they%20form%20one%20%E2%80%9CQaum%E2%80%99%20and%20one%20nation%E2%80%A6the%20Prophet%20said%20that%20he%20extended%20the%20hands%20of%20friendship%20to%20all%20those%20who%20lived%20in%20the%20vicinity%20of%20Medina%20and%20declared%20that%20we%20should%20be%20%E2%80%98Umma%20Vahidah%E2%80%99%2C%20one%20people.%E2%80%9D%20(p.166%20and%20136).%20He%20returned%20to%20the%20theme%20again%20and%20again%2C%20indeed%20it%20became%20the%20leitmotif%20of%20his%20thought%20process.%20Drawing%20attention%20to%20India%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%9Ccomposite%20culture%E2%80%9D%2C%20that%2C%20he%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CHindus%20and%20Muslims%20(have)%20been%20shaping%20for%20the%20last%20one%20thousand%20years%20and%20more%E2%80%9D%2C%20he%20stressed%20that%20the%20Muslims%20have%20been%20%E2%80%9Cproud%20and%20active%20partners%E2%80%9D%20in%20forging%20a%20%E2%80%9Csyncretic%20culture%20which%20occupies%20a%20distinctly%20distinguished%20place%E2%80%9D.%20(p.166)%20This%2C%20he%20concluded%2C%20had%20given%20rise%20to%20the%20two%20communities%20sharing%20%E2%80%9Ca%20common%20nationality%E2%80%9D%20(p.160).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20that%20while%20%E2%80%9Cas%20a%20Muslim%2C%20I%20have%20a%20special%20identity%E2%80%A6I%20am%20equally%20proud%20of%20the%20fact%20that%20I%20am%20an%20Indian%2C%20an%20essential%20part%20of%20the%20indivisible%20unity%20of%20Indian%20nationhood%E2%80%9D%20(p.160).%20He%20also%20punctured%20(p.%20156)%20the%20argument%20for%20Muslim%20separatism%2C%20holding%20incontrovertibly%20that%20as%20%E2%80%9CMuslims%20number%20between%20eight%20and%20nine%20crores%E2%80%9D%2C%20(how)%20%E2%80%9Ccan%20such%20a%20vast%20mass%20of%20humanity%20have%20any%20legitimate%20reason%20for%20apprehension%20that%20in%20a%20free%20and%20independent%20India%20it%20may%20not%20be%20possible%20to%20protect%20its%20rights%20and%20interests%3F%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Funcategorised%2Finterview-irfan-habib-ajoy%5C%22%3EInterview%3A%20Irfan%20Habib%20Debunks%20RSS%E2%80%99s%20Nationalism%20and%20Their%20Attempts%20to%20Rewrite%20History%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20implied%20that%20if%20the%20community%20divided%20into%20three%2C%20as%20it%20has%20done%20in%20the%20Partition%20of%20India%20in%201947%20and%20the%20Partition%20of%20Pakistan%20in%201971%2C%20Muslim%20vulnerability%20in%20the%20subcontinent%20would%20only%20increase.%20Hence%20his%20clarion%20call%3A%20%E2%80%9CThe%20need%20of%20the%20hour%20is%20a%20single%20and%20united%20nationhood%E2%80%9D.%20Jinnah%20fiercely%20disagreed%2C%20which%20is%20why%20Pakistani%20nationhood%20not%20only%20fragmented%20but%20remained%20fractured%2C%20and%20in%20today%E2%80%99s%20India%20the%20future%20of%20the%20community%20is%20fragile.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAzad%20mourned.%20From%20the%20steps%20of%20the%20Jama%20Masjid%2C%20he%20spoke%20to%20his%20community%20in%20October%201947%2C%20within%20weeks%20of%20Partition%20(p.266)%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EToday%2C%20when%20I%20see%20your%20ashen%20faces%20and%20desolation%20in%20your%20hearts%2C%20my%20mind%20goes%20back%20to%20the%20past.%20%E2%80%A6I%20had%20warned%20you%20how%20the%20forces%20of%20poison%20unleashed%20by%20sinister%20designs%20would%20lead%20to%20the%20tragedy%20of%20Partition%2C%20but%20you%20refused%20to%20listen%20to%20me.%20You%20relied%20on%20your%20ignorance%20and%20today%20you%20feel%20as%20though%20you%20are%20threatened%20by%20new%20dangers%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20indeed%20they%20are%20in%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1692097256000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F07%2F28185829%2Fcollage-13.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Freview-irfan-habibs-maulana-azad-a-life-is-a-voice-of-reason-and-unity-in-times-of-hate%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22An%20exploration%20of%20different%20interpretations%20of%20basic%20Islamic%20texts%20in%20the%20light%20of%20rationalism%20became%20gradually%20but%20definitively%20the%20drumbeat%20of%20Azad%E2%80%99s%20thinking.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Freview-irfan-habibs-maulana-azad-a-life-is-a-voice-of-reason-and-unity-in-times-of-hate%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Amid%20NEET%20Row%2C%20Tamil%20Nadu%20CM%20Stalin%20Wants%20Education%20Shifted%20from%20Concurrent%20to%20State%20List%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F05%2F06200018%2FScreenshot-2022-05-06-at-8.00.11-PM.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3ETamil%20Nadu%20chief%20minister%20M.K.%20Stalin%20said%20moving%20education%20to%20the%20State%20List%20from%20the%20Concurrent%20List%20of%20the%20Constitution%20is%20the%20way%20forward%20to%20scrap%20the%20National%20Eligibility%20cum%20Entrance%20Test%20(NEET)%20during%20his%20Independence%20Day%20address%20in%20Chennai%20on%20Tuesday%2C%20August%2015%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livemint.com%2Fnews%2Findia%2Fneet-could-be-scrapped-only-if-tamil-nadu-cm-mk-stali